      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Treasury ¶ Melbourne ¶ , ¶  ¶ July 15th ¶ 1864. ¶ A.B. ¶ Memorandum ¶ —A| ¶ c ¶  ¶ M 1712/13 ¶ Instead of charging a portion of the cost of the Horse to the item for "Incidental Expenses", the proper ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.07.15<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Edward Symonds</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">H64/7313, unit 31, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">Treasury</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-style: italic; ">Melbourne</seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">,</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>July 15th<seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1864.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">A.B.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">Memorandum</seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">—A|</seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">c<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>M 1712/13</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Instead of charging a portion of the cost of the Horse to the item for "Incidental Expenses", the proper course would be to move the Hon, the Cf Secy<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Chief Secretary.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to issue a "Transfer authority" to transfer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>£3<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from "Incidentals" to the item, "Purchase of a draught horse", so that the expenditure may be brought under instead.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. McCulloch, 3 March 1864 (in this edition as 64-03-03a) requested funds to buy a draught horse for garden work to replace the existing aged animal. A sum of £30 was provided as an "additional estimate", and M to J. McCulloch, 8 June 1864 (in this edition as 64-06-08a) sought authority to proceed. However, an additional £3<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>proved to be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>needed. M followed the advice from Symonds in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to J. McCulloch, 26 July 1864 (in this edition as 64-07-26b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">E. S Symonds</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Director of the Botanic Gardens</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">N.B.—It is requested that this Memorandum may be returned with the account and reply.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
